<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ASSEMBLE -
        DRIVE PINION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>DRIVE PINION</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1401222">Figure 22</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1401222" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1401222" filename="../figg14/g1401222.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 22. Drive Pinion Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lubricate parts with gear lube during reassembly. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000
                    Master Service Manual. When installing bearing cones and pilot bearing, use properly sized sleeves
                    that only contact the inner bearing race.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before installing cups, check for burrs on bearing surfaces and remove. Press bearing cups
                in cage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401223">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401223" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401223" filename="../figg14/g1401223.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Install Bearing Cups</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press pilot bearing on pinion. Stake bearing using staking tool (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401224">Figure 24</hotlnk>). Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401225">Figure 25</hotlnk>
                for stake pattern.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401224" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401224" filename="../figg14/g1401224.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Install Pilot Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1401225" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401225" filename="../figg14/g1401225.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Pinion Pilot Bearing Stake Pattern</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust pinion bearing preload by performing
                <hotlnk document="s14012_17.xml" xrefid="hl1401204">TRIAL BUILD-UP TEST
                    <xref refid="hl1401204"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
